laboratory_examinations.findings: Showing excess blasts and cytogenetic findings of translocation 3;5 and +WT-1 mutation, consistent with myelodysplastic syndrome.

findings.liver: Suggestion of mild diffuse fatty liver. Contour of the liver is smooth. No focal liver mass.
findings.bile_ducts: No intrahepatic biliary dilation. Common hepatic duct measures 4 mm; distal common bile duct measures 1.0 cm.
findings.gallbladder: Stones and biliary sludge in the distended gallbladder with wall edema. Gallbladder wall thickening and edema measuring 0.3 cm to 0.4 cm.
findings.pancreas: Imaged portion appears within normal limits.
findings.kidneys: Right kidney measures 12 cm; left kidney measures 12 cm. No evidence of hydronephrosis.
